"is_placeholder":true,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"display_name":"William Dwight Evans","first_name":"William","middle_name":"Dwight","last_name":"Evans","married_names":[],"gender":"male"},"birth":{"year":1849,"country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1861,"country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM176","plot_notes":"Berlin Corner Cemetery, Berlin Corners VT."},"gender":"male","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":true,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":true,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_john_talcott":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0},"parents":{"father_id":"X02383","mother_id":"TD0124"},"marriages":[],"tags":["died_young"],"research_tags":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"William died young","body":"William died in 1861, aged about twelve."}],"cross_connections":[],"naming_inspiration":[{"name_element":"Dwight","inspired_by_id":"TD0131","description":"Middle name 'Dwight' honors his maternal uncle Timothy Dwight Hobart (1826-1853), who died at twenty-seven while preparing at Andover for the ministry — himself named in honor of Yale's Timothy Dwight."}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"documents":[],"quotes":[],"statues":[],"slug":"william-dwight-evans-td0164"}},"burialCemetery":{"id":"CEM176","name":"Berlin Corner Cemetery","city":"Berlin Corners","county":"Washington","state":"Vermont","country":"United States","primary_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/cemetery/641556/berlin-corner-cemetery","hooker_connections":["T01387","TD0120","TD0124","TD0129","TD0158","TD0159","TD0160","TD0161","TD0162","TD0163","TD0164","TD0200","X01832","X02368","X02370","X02383","X02384","X02409"],"notes":"Berlin Corner Cemetery, Berlin Corners Vermont. Burial site of the Perrin-Hobart founding family of Berlin VT — Zachariah Perrin Esq. (X01832, Berlin VT 1789 founder, Rev War vet, d.1838 age 90), his wife Mary Talcott Perrin (T01387, d.1828), their daughter Betsey Perrin Hobart (TD0120, d.1876), her husband Rev. James Hobart (X02368, Berlin VT first settled minister, d.1862 age 95), their son David Hobart (TD0129, d.1901), and his wife Caroline Reed Hobart (X02370, d.1898). Three Perrin-Hobart generations. [pilot100] Backfilled with Evans/Yale Berlin VT generation: Dr. Ira Evans Sr. (X02383) and Emeline Hobart Evans (TD0124, daughter of Rev. James + Betsey Hobart); their seven children including 4 died young/childhood/infancy (Mary E., Ira Jr., J. Annette, William Dwight) and 3 adult-lifespan (Mary Emeline Evans Yale + her Civil War vet husband Capt. Thomas Blossom Yale 108th NY Inf, Edward P. Evans 10th VT Inf wounded Cold Harbor, and Civil War Medal of Honor recipient Ira Hobart Evans TD0163 who died San Diego CA 1922 and was returned to Berlin Corner per his wishes). Cemetery now spans four generations of Hobart-Evans-Yale family across ~150 years."},"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}